'''Scott Smith''' (born 21 July 1995) is a Scottish [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Elgin City F.C.|Elgin City]] as a [[midfielder]]. Smith formerly played for [[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]] until being released in February 2016. A product of the Dundee United youth system, he has also played for [[Forfar Athletic F.C.|Forfar Athletic]], and [[Airdrieonians F.C.|Airdrieonians]] on loan.

==Early life and career==
Smith was born in [[Perth, Scotland|Perth]] and played for Longforgan Boys Club with future teammate [[Scott Fraser (footballer, born 1995)|Scott Fraser]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://worldinsport.com/scott-fraser-dundee-united-review/|title=Scott Fraser Dundee United Review|last=James|first=Joseph|website=World in Sport|date=14 May 2014|accessdate=18 July 2014}}</ref> before joining the Dundee United youth system. Youth coach [[Ian Cathro]] rated him as highly as Dundee United's most promising talents [[Ryan Gauld]] and [[John Souttar]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2518538/Ryan-Gauld-Dundee-Uniteds-Baby-Messi-wowed-Brechin-Under-Nines.html|title=The Gauld standard: Dundee United's Baby Messi first wowed at Brechin Under-Nines (and wasn’t their sole star of the future)|last=Marjoribanks|first=Brian|website=Daily Mail|date=5 December 2013|accessdate=18 July 2014}}</ref> He continued to impress and went on to sign a professional contract in June 2011.<ref>{{cite web|title=Scott Smith|url=http://www.dundeeunitedfc.co.uk/index.asp?tm=167&ID=387|work=Dundee United F.C. official website|accessdate=30 April 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140502010210/http://www.dundeeunitedfc.co.uk/index.asp?tm=167&ID=387|archivedate=2 May 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref>

==Playing career==
Smith made his first team debut as a late substitute against [[Heart of Midlothian F.C.|Heart of Midlothian]] in March 2014.<ref>{{cite web|title=Hearts 1–2 Dundee United|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/26572819|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=30 April 2014}}</ref> Soon after, he signed a contract extension to keep him at the club until 2016<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thecourier.co.uk/sport/football/dundee-united/dundee-united-extend-duo-s-deals-1.302960|title=Dundee United extend duo's deals|last=Robertson|first=Neil|website=The Courier|date=4 April 2014|accessdate=18 July 2014}}</ref> and again made a late appearance for the first team against [[Aberdeen F.C.|Aberdeen]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.scotsman.com/sport/football/spfl/dundee-united-1-3-aberdeen-vernon-scores-three-1-3400811|title=Dundee United 1–3 Aberdeen: Vernon scores three|last=Gordon|first=Moira|website=The Scotsman|date=6 May 2014|accessdate=18 July 2014}}</ref>

On 6 November 2014, Smith joined [[Forfar Athletic F.C.|Forfar Athletic]] on loan until January 2015.<ref>{{cite web|title=Scott Smith joins 'Loons' on loan|url=http://www.forfarathletic.co.uk/index.php?option=com_flexicontent&view=items&cid=6%3Anews&id=1578%3Ascott-smith-joins-loons-on-loan&Itemid=27|publisher=Forfar Athletic F.C.|date=6 November 2014|accessdate=19 November 2014}}</ref> He made his debut on 8 November 2014, in a 2–0 defeat against [[Greenock Morton F.C.|Greenock Morton]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Greenock Morton 2 Forfar Athletic 0|url=http://www.forfarathletic.co.uk/index.php?option=com_flexicontent&view=items&cid=10:fixtures-and-reports&id=1582:851&Itemid=28|publisher=Forfar Athletic F.C.|last=Davidson|first=Cameron|date=9 November 2014|accessdate=19 November 2014}}</ref>

On 26 August 2015, Smith signed on loan for [[Airdrieonians F.C.|Airdrieonians]] until January 2016.<ref>{{cite web|title=scott smith signs loan deal|url=http://airdriefc.com/news/2015/08/scottsmith|publisher=Airdrieonians F.C.|date=26 August 2015|accessdate=26 August 2015}}</ref> After returning from Airdrie, Smith was released by Dundee United in February 2016.<ref>{{cite news|title=Scott Smith leaves United|url=http://dufc.co/news/scott-smith-leaves-united/|accessdate=1 February 2016|publisher=Dundee United F.C.|date=1 February 2016}}</ref> In March 2016, Smith returned to Forfar Athletic, signing a short-term contract.<ref>{{cite news|title=Smith signs for Forfar |url=http://spfl.co.uk/news/article/smith-signs-for-forfar/ |accessdate=23 March 2016 |publisher=spfl.co.uk |date=23 March 2016}}</ref> He left Forfar at the end of the [[2015–16 in Scottish football|2015–16 season]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/36412965 |title=Scottish League Two ins and outs – summer 2016 |first=Clive |last=Lindsay |publisher=BBC Sport |accessdate=25 July 2016}}</ref> signing for [[Elgin City F.C.|Elgin City]] in July 2016.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.northern-scot.co.uk/Sport/Football/Two-more-new-signings-for-Elgin-City-13072016.htm |title=Two more new signings for Elgin City |first=Craig |last=Christie |work=The Northern Scot |date=13 July 2016 |accessdate=25 July 2016}}</ref>

